Updates the Fortran standard compilation flag from Fortran 2003 (`-std=f2003`) to Fortran 2018 (`-std=f2018`).

Original issue: When compiling the `hipsparse_fortran` bindings with modern compiler toolchains (like GCC 14),
restricting the standard to Fortran 2003 causes the build to fail. This is typically due to the compiler's stricter
enforcement of language standards or the use of newer Fortran syntax within the upstream source files.

Author: Aayush Joglekar (aayush.joglekar@surf.nl)

diff --git a/library/CMakeLists.txt b/library/CMakeLists.txt
index 6d5665c..ad633fd 100644
--- a/library/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/library/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -56,7 +56,7 @@ set(CMAKE_Fortran_MODULE_DIRECTORY ${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR}/include/hipsparse)
 add_library(hipsparse_fortran OBJECT ${hipsparse_fortran_source})
 
 # Target compile options
-target_compile_options(hipsparse_fortran PRIVATE -std=f2003 -ffree-form -cpp)
+target_compile_options(hipsparse_fortran PRIVATE -std=f2018 -ffree-form -cpp)
 endif()
 
 # Create hipSPARSE library
